input.name: handle
input.narrative: The integer handle identifying the instance which should have its window displayed. The default of zero indicates the currently active instance.

input.name: handle
input.narrative: The integer handle identifying the instance on which the required workbook should be opened. The default of zero indicates the currently active instance.

input.name: File name
input.narrative: The path and name of the file which should be opened.

output.name: Workbook Name
output.narrative: The name used by Excel to identify the workbook - usually this is the file name (without the path).

input.name: handle
input.narrative: The integer handle identifying the instance from which the required cell value should be retrieved. The default of zero indicates the currently active instance.

input.name: Cell Reference
input.narrative: The cell reference indicating which cell's value should be retrieved. An empty value indicates that the currently active cell's value should be retrieved.

output.name: Value
output.narrative: The (unformatted) value from the required cell.
